---
import { Image } from 'astro:assets'

import commandBg from '@images/stock/commandBg.png'

const t1 =
  'This office provides dedicated and trained professional security personal in all areas under the above heading. Our personal are experienced officers that can operate, control, monitor and perform functions from simple monitoring to responding to complete command and control centers, which can dispatch, monitor, record and store data and control from a single central location. Officers are training in a variety of monitoring and recording equipment, as well as communications equipment, devices and procedures. Officers are trained and schooled in crises situations, including such as emergencies as fire and or earthquake evacuations. Procedures and protocols, range from local security command and control to notifications and assistance to police, fire, medical and first responders.'

const t2 =
  ' Whether it is a dispatch center, camera monitoring assignment or the solitary security officer on a post, they all have one thing in common, 24-7-365 communication. Every employee has the availability of communication at anytime that they are on duty, via radio or cellular phone. Their supervisors, and in some cases, their clients, are available at all times if so needed or notifications need to be made. In turn supervisors are able to contact management if needed anytime. Clients may contact the security officer, the supervisor or management at anytime.'

const t3 =
  'Needless to say, communications are critical in the security business. Communications in written form, i.e; DAR’s and Reports are submitted daily.'

const t4 =
  'Whatever your needs are, National 50 Security and Investigations Inc. will work with you to provide a security plan to fit your individual security needs.'
---
  {/* Blue Section Command and Control*/}
  <section class="bg-dark-900 grid grid-cols-2">
    <div class="relative">
    <Image
          src={commandBg}
          alt="description"
          class="absolute inset-0 h-full w-full object-cover object-center fade-in-anim-left"
        />
      </div>
    <div class="p-16 relative z-10">
      <div class="flex w-full justify-center">
        <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-white fade-in-anim-right ">
          COMMAND AND CONTROL, DISPATCH, COMMUNICATION AND MONITORING
        </h1>
      </div>
      {/* Project description */}
      <div class="mx-auto mt-6 flex w-full flex-wrap">
        <div class="mx-auto w-full">
          <p
            class="mb-6 text-2xl font-normal tracking-tight text-white lg:leading-tight fade-in-anim-right"
          >
            This office provides dedicated and trained professional security
            personal in all areas under the above heading. Our personal are
            experienced officers that can operate, control, monitor and perform
            functions from simple monitoring to responding to complete command
            and control centers, which can dispatch, monitor, record and store
            data and control from a single central location. Officers are
            training in a variety of monitoring and recording equipment, as well
            as communications equipment, devices and procedures. Officers are
            trained and schooled in crises situations, including such as
            emergencies as fire and or earthquake evacuations. Procedures and
            protocols, range from local security command and control to
            notifications and assistance to police, fire, medical and first
            responders.
          </p>
          <p
            class="mb-6 text-2xl font-normal tracking-tight text-white lg:leading-tight fade-in-anim-right"
          >
            Whether it is a dispatch center, camera monitoring assignment or the
            solitary security officer on a post, they all have one thing in
            common, 24-7-365 communication. Every employee has the availability
            of communication at anytime that they are on duty, via radio or
            cellular phone. Their supervisors, and in some cases, their clients,
            are available at all times if so needed or notifications need to be
            made. In turn supervisors are able to contact management if needed
            anytime. Clients may contact the security officer, the supervisor or
            management at anytime.
          </p>
          <p
            class="mb-6 text-2xl font-normal tracking-tight text-white lg:leading-tight fade-in-anim-right"
          >
            Needless to say, communications are critical in the security
            business. Communications in written form, i.e; DAR’s and Reports are
            submitted daily.
          </p>
          <p
            class="mb-6 text-2xl font-normal tracking-tight text-white lg:leading-tight fade-in-anim-right"
          >
            Whatever your needs are, National 50 Security and Investigations
            Inc. will work with you to provide a security plan to fit your
            individual security needs.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


<style>

  .fade-in-anim-left {
    view-timeline: --subjectReveal block;
    animation-timeline: --subjectReveal;
  
    animation-name: fadein-left;
    animation-fill-mode: both;
    animation-duration: 1ms; /* Firefox requires this to apply the animation */
    animation-range: entry 25% cover 50% ;
  }

  .fade-in-anim-right {
    view-timeline: --subjectReveal block;
    animation-timeline: --subjectReveal;
  
    animation-name: fadein-right;
    animation-fill-mode: both;
    animation-duration: 1ms; /* Firefox requires this to apply the animation */
    animation-range: entry 25% cover 50% ;
  }

  .fade-in-anim-center {
    view-timeline: --subjectReveal block;
    animation-timeline: --subjectReveal;
  
    animation-name: fadein-center;
    animation-fill-mode: both;
    animation-duration: 1ms; /* Firefox requires this to apply the animation */
    animation-range: entry 15% cover 60% ;
  }
  .fade-in-anim {
    view-timeline: --subjectReveal block;
    animation-timeline: --subjectReveal;
  
    animation-name: fadein;
    animation-fill-mode: both;
    animation-duration: 1ms; /* Firefox requires this to apply the animation */
    animation-range: entry 25% cover 50% ;
  }
  
  @keyframes fadein-left {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateX(-300px);
  }

  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateX(0);
  }
}

@keyframes fadein-right {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateX(300px);
  }

  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateX(0);
  }
}

@keyframes fadein-center {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateY(40px);
    
  }

  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateY(0);
    
  }
}

@keyframes fadein {
  from {
    opacity: 0;
    transform: scale(0.5);
  }

  to {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: scale(1);
  }
}


  
  </style>
